Struggle veteran Andrew Mlangeni has passed on. He was admitted to 1 Military Hospital in Pretoria following an abdominal complaint. Mlangeni was the last surviving Rivonia Trialist who spent more than 20 years on Robben Island after his conviction at the Treason Trial in 1964. He turned 95 on June 6. In the video below is the announcement of Mlangeniâ€™s death: 